review_blob: Quite a nice beer, though it does tend to be overpriced.  An interestingly different flavour and pleasing finish.
A very nice beer, quite heavy bodied, with a good bitter aftertaste.  In draught form, it is one of the smoothest beers i've tasted.
A very dissapointing beer, the initial pleasing bitter taste gives way to an unpleasant chemical aftertaste.
A fairly ordinarly beer, not bad, by midstrength standards, but far from impressive.
Quite good in flavour, though the low joule does seem to leave the beer lacking in some aspects.  A strangely filling beer.
Not my kind of beer, too much of a vegimite flavour, though I don't usually mind a darkish ale
A very unusual aftertaste, though a quite drinkable beer. Best drunk while it's on the verge of freezing
A reasonably nice beer, assuming you can find someone selling it for the right price.  Wouldn't go out of my way to get it
Not a bad beer, much better on tap than bottled, tinnies offer some salvation from the flat taste of the stubbies.
Possibly the best beer ever.  I'd go tinnies over stubbies for the extra sharpness, I'll drink it at room temp, i'll drink it frozen.  Man this beer owns
